# Groove Lab chord strip corner embeds (LOCKED — user verified)

Green **OrchidChordStrip** (`grooveBranding`) hosts four fixed corner controls in **Creation Station / Groove Lab**. User positioned and verified layout — **do not move, re-stack, or re-enable drag** unless they explicitly ask.

## Placement system (do not replace)

**Mixer zone** (bottom of green strip): inline column in `OrchidChordStrip` — not a corner overlay.

| Row | Content |
|-----|---------|
| Toolbar (above CH 33–48 rail) | MET + `OrchidTransportControls` + **Mixer** toggle — right-aligned |
| Rail | `GrooveLabChannelRail` embed — faders + channel select |
| Popup (when Mixer open) | `GrooveLabMixerPanel` — `position: absolute`, `bottom: 100%` of mixer section (above toolbar + rail) |

**Forbidden:** moving transport/Mixer back to `GrooveLabDraggableCornerPanel` bottom-corner anchors unless the user asks.

## Mixer (CH 33–48)

- Toggle + **`GrooveLabMixerPanel`** — 16 lanes, SUB/CHORD/MELODY labels
- Volumes via `channelVolumes` / `setChannelVolume` from `useMasterClock()` when embedded in Creation Station
- Pan: `groove-lab-channel-pans-v1` + `__daMusicChannelPans`

## Related wiring (touch only if mixer/routing work continues)

- `GrooveLabScreen` → `OrchidPerformancePanel` → `OrchidChordStrip` props
- `CreationStationScreen` passes `channelVolumes` / `setChannelVolume` into `GrooveLabScreen`

## Forbidden without explicit user request

- Re-enabling drag (removing `embedded` or showing grip handles)
- Splitting transport off the Mixer stack into a separate corner panel (use the combined column on `groove-lab-mixer-btn-pos`)
- Changing defaultRight/defaultBottom or storage keys (breaks saved layout)
- Substituting Beat Lab mixer for Groove Lab CH 33–48 panel
